    version="1.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&#xD;
    style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: DE; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>The&#xD;
    business processes description must include: including participants and actors involved, control flow with sequence of&#xD;
    activities and messages between pools, flow decisions and business rules.&amp;nbsp;It is recommended to use process&#xD;
    patterns (workflow patterns) to help in various modeling aspects of business processes. The boundaries of business are&#xD;
    clearly stated, indicating who and what interacts with the organization, specifying processes both in natural language&#xD;
    and graphically using a Business Process Modeler tool (BizAgi, ARIS, Visual Paradigm, etc.). QVT transformations are&#xD;
    defined to generate services models specified in the OMG SoaML standard from business process models specified in BPMN,&#xD;
    that can be executed in the Eclipse environment.&lt;/span>&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&#xD;
    style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: DE; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>Example&#xD;
    of a BPMN busines process model for a Reseller (adapted from Weske, 2007):&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/ResellerBusinessProcessAchicado.jpg&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;451&quot; />&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>It is recommended to use process patterns (workflow patterns, van der Aalst et. al, 2003) to help in various modeling&#xD;
aspects of business processes, reusing knowledge and best solutions.</keyConsiderations>
  <sections xmi:id="_wIO_YPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw" name="Identify participants and actors involved"
      guid="_wIO_YPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_xoAwEPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw" name="Identify activities to be performed "
      guid="_xoAwEPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_za3NwPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw" name="Identify the sequence of activities realization"
      guid="_za3NwPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_0y-QMPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw" name="Identify decision nodes in the flow"
      guid="_0y-QMPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_2XXbIPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw" name="Identify message interaction with other participants (if any)"
      guid="_2XXbIPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_4C3ToPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw" name="Identify business rules" guid="_4C3ToPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_50LgQPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw" name="New Step" guid="_50LgQPAUEeWvO5pgCiF2Uw"/>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&#xD;
    style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: DE; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>To&#xD;
    understand and describe the business processes in the organization, mainly those related to the application being&#xD;
    developed, specifying the business process models using&amp;nbsp;the Business Process Modeling Notation (BPMN)&lt;/span>.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
  <alternatives>&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&#xD;
style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: DE; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>The&#xD;
notation used to specify the business process models from which to generate SoaML services models is BPMN. Other notations&#xD;
could be used, but the QVT transformations defined could not then be executed.&lt;/span></alternatives>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
